-- Cemig Plans to Buy Additional 9.75% Stake in Light From Enlighted Partners
-- B y   L a u r a   P r i c e
-- 2010-10-07T13:09:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-07/cemig-plans-to-buy-additional-9-75-stake-in-light-from-enlighted-partners.html
Cia. Energetica de Minas Gerais  said
Enlighted Partners Venture Capital LLC decided to exercise a put
option to sell Cemig a stake in Light SA.  Cemig, based in Belo Horizonte, Brazil, said on March 24 it
had the option to buy 19.9 million voting shares, or an
additional 9.75 percent stake in Light through Newark, Delaware-
based Luce Investment Fund from Enlighted. Cemig said in March
it may pay $340.5 million for the stake.  The conclusion of the deal is subject to certain
conditions, Cemig said in a regulatory filing today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
